# Project context for Claude Code

> Pointer file. Real context lives in `AGENTS.md` and `.ai-factory/`.

This project follows the AGENTS.md standard. Claude Code reads BOTH this file AND `AGENTS.md` at session start. To avoid drift between them, this file contains no rules — only pointers.

## Source of truth

- **`AGENTS.md`** — what we're building, workflow, slim list of rules
- **`.ai-factory/DESCRIPTION.md`** — stack, hard constraints, non-goals
- **`.ai-factory/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — layer rules, dependency direction
- **`.ai-factory/RULES.md`** — code rules R1–R20 (enforced)

## Workflow

Use AI Factory commands for non-trivial changes:
- `/aif-plan <task>` — plan + branch
- `/aif-implement` — execute step-by-step
- `/aif-verify` — REQUIRED before commit (sub-agents validate RULES.md, run audit-ai-docs)
- `/aif-fix <error>` — targeted fix
- `/aif-commit` — final commit

Don't bypass `/aif-verify` with `--no-verify`. If a rule is incompatible with the task — discuss via `/aif-rules`, not skip.

## What NOT to put here

- Code style → ESLint/Prettier configs
- Test conventions → `RULES.md` R4 + `audit-ai-docs.sh`
- Architectural rules → `dependency-cruiser` + `RULES.md` R3
- Project description → `AGENTS.md` + `.ai-factory/DESCRIPTION.md`

`CLAUDE.md` is a pointer. Real rules are enforced, not described.
